        [
          "Classification",
          "Intelligent Tutoring System",
          "Correct Ansewr in Next Question",
          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect (0)",
          "4151 ASSISTments2009 learners",
          "ASSISTments",
          "Answer Sequences, LMS logs",
          "[user_id, problem_id, correct, attempt_count, first_response, first_action]",
          "DKVMN, while interesting as an approach, has the issue of not considering additional features relative to sequences of answers - the knowledge status.",
          "The authors propose a small change to DKVMN that not only includes sequences of answersa to create both matrices, but also considers additional behavioral information in order to obtain a better value matrix.",
          "The model starts with the prediction section of whether a question will be correct or not.\n\nThis is followed by a Clustering module that is meant to calculate learning ability and group students into one of 3 groups.\n\n",
          "BKT, DKT, DKVMN, DKT-F, DKT-DSC, DKVMN-LA",
          "5-Fold Cross-Validation",
          "{AUC: 0.919 - DKVMN-LA}",
          "Authors perform 4 distinct experiments:\n\n1. Comparison od DKVMN-LA with other models in the literature.\n\n2. Comparison of DKVMN-LA with DKT-LA.\n\n3. Analysis of the model suing different segment lengths.\n\n4. Changes with different feature splicings.\n\nDKVMN-LA wiuth all features and segment length 5 outperforms all others.",
          "Limited number of Benchmark Datasets.\n\nRoom for improvement in behavioral features being considered. \n\nOpportunity for refinement both at the stage of correctedness prediction AND LEarning Ability clustering."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 7
    }
