    {
      "id": "1944750c-f3ba-801e-bc5f-c2c7eee159e0",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Out of all models in KT that existed in 2022, Dynamic Key-Value Memory Networks (DKVMN) have been argued to be state-of-the-art. A drawback of these models is that they seem to not consider learning abilities or behavioral features collected by ITS. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "1944750c-f3ba-801e-bc5f-c2c7eee159e0",
        "parent": {
          "type": "page_id",
          "page_id": "18b4750c-f3ba-80b6-a8a8-dc0f6228781d"
        },
        "created_time": "2025-02-08T23:37:00.000Z",
        "last_edited_time": "2025-02-08T23:40:00.000Z",
        "created_by": {
          "object": "user",
